[1631.355153, "o", "\u001b[3;17Hd\u001b[4;23Hd.apache.org/\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdo\u001b[m\u000fcs/2.4/> for detailed\u001b[6;19Hd.apache.org/\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdo\u001b[m\u000fcs/2.4/mod/d\u001b[7;9Hdiscussion of each configuration d\u001b[9;20Hd the instructions in here without understand\u001b[10;14H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mo\u001b[m\u000f.  They're here only as hints or remind\u001b[11;23H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mo\u001b[m\u000fcs. You have been warned\u001b[13;19Hd\u001b[14;53Hd\u001b[15;58H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mo\u001b[16;46H\u001b[m\u000fded\u001b[17;65Hd\u001b[19;21Hd\u001b[22;30Hdirectory tree und\u001b[23;27Hd\u001b[25;11Hdd a slash at the end of the d\u001b[26;29Hdisk, be sure to specify a local d\u001b[27;9Hdirective, if file-based mutexes are used\u001b[28;36Hd daemons, you will need\u001b[29;11Hd\u001b[31;22H\u001b[92md\u001b[34;50H\u001b[m\u000fd mutex file d\u001b[35;9Hdividual mutexes, or change the global d\u001b[37;15Hd change the directory if mutexes are file-based and the d\u001b[38;14Hdirectory is not on a local d\u001b[41;9Hdefault:/run/httpd\u001b[44;28Hd Apache to specific IP addresses and\u001b[45;16Hd of the d\u001b[46;3Hd\u001b[48;41Hdd\u001b[49;45Hd IP add\u001b[55;16Hd\u001b[57;46Hd\u001b[58;26Hding `LoadMod\u001b[59;3Hdirectives contained in it are actually available _before_ they are used\u001b[60;21Hd modules (those listed by `httpd -l') \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdo\u001b[m\u000f not need\u001b[61;12Hded\u001b[64;6HdModule foo_module modules/mod\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f4,36\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
[1631.714954, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000fc"]
[1631.721194, "o", "\u001b[4;38H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mc\u001b[6;34Hc\u001b[10;13H\u001b[m\u000fdo\u001b[11;24H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mc\u001b[15;57H\u001b[m\u000fdo\u001b[60;60Hdo\u001b[67;5H\u001b[?25h"]
[1631.81451, "o", "\u001b[?25lu"]
[1631.821182, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f alias_module modules/mod_alias.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f rewrite_module modules/mod_rewrite.so\u001b[26X\r\n\u001b[65X\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<IfModule\u001b[m\u000f unixd_module\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[48X\u001b[5;2H\u001b[20X\u001b[6;3HIf you wish httpd to run as a different user or group, you must run\u001b[7;3Hhttpd as root initially and it will switch.      \u001b[9;3HUser/Group: The name (or #number) of the user/group to run httpd as.\u001b[10;3HIt is usually good practice to create a dedicated user and group for\u001b[6X\u001b[11;3Hrunning httpd, as with most system services.    \r\n\n\u001b[96mUser\u001b[m\u000f http\u001b[63X\r\n\u001b[96mGroup\u001b[m\u000f http\u001b[66X\r\n\u001b[70X\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</IfModule>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[61X\r\n\u001b[72X\u001b[18;3H'Main' server configuration\u001b[48X\u001b[19;2H\u001b[43X\r\n# The directives in this section set up the values used by the 'main'\u001b[21;2H server, which responds to any requests that aren't handled by a\u001b[22;3H<VirtualHost> definition.  These values also provide defaults for \u001b[23;3Hany <VirtualHost> containers you may define later in the file.\u001b[25;3HAll of these directives may appear inside <VirtualHost> containers,\u001b[26;3Hin which case these default settings will be overridden for the\u001b[7X\u001b[27;3Hvirtual host being defined.\u001b[47X\u001b[28;2H\u001b[71X\r\n\u001b[16X\n\n# ServerAdmin: Your address, where problems with the server should be\r\n# e-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such\u001b[33;2H as error \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdocu\u001b[m\u000fments.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\u001b[34;2H\u001b[70X\r\n\u001b[96mServerAdmin\u001b[m\u000f you@\u001b[96mexample\u001b[m\u000f.com\u001b[28X\r\n \n\u001b[77X\u001b[38;3HServerName gives the name and port that the server uses to identify itself.\u001b[39;3HThis can often be determined automatically, but we recommend you specify\u001b[40;2H it explicitly to prevent problems during startup.\u001b[41;2H\u001b[25X\r\n# If your host doesn't have a registered DNS name, enter its IP address here.\u001b[44;2HServerName www.example.com:80\u001b[37X\r\n\u001b[59X\u001b[46;2H\u001b[11X\n Deny access to the entirety of your server's filesystem. You must\u001b[48;3Hexplicitly permit access to web content directories in other     \u001b[49;3H<Directory> blocks below.\u001b[32X\r\n\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Directory\u001b[m\u000f /\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[9X\r\n    \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f none\u001b[53;5H\u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all denied\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</Directory>\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[57;3HNote that from this point forward you must specifically allow\u001b[15X\u001b[58;3Hparticular features to be enabled - so if something's not working as  \u001b[59;3Hyou might expect, make sure that you have specifically enabled it\u001b[8X\u001b[60;3Hbelow.\u001b[62X\u001b[61;2H\u001b[19X\r\n \n\u001b[9X\u001b[64;3HDocumentRoot: The directory out of which you will serve your\u001b[65;2H \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdocu\u001b[m\u000fments. By default, all requests are taken from this directory, but\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f220,12         39%\u001b[67;6H\u001b[?25h"]
[1632.014876, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000fm"]
