[1637.035997, "o", "\u001b[1;2H e-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such\u001b[2;3Has error documents.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\u001b[25X\u001b[3;2H\u001b[64X\r\n\u001b[96mServerAdmin\u001b[m\u000f you@\u001b[96mexample\u001b[m\u000f.com\u001b[44X\r\n\u001b[21X\u001b[6;2H\u001b[59X\u001b[7;3HServerName gives the name and port that the server uses to identify itself.\u001b[8;2H This can often be determined automatically, but we recommend you specify\u001b[9;3Hit explicitly to prevent problems during startup.\u001b[16X\u001b[10;2H\u001b[75X\u001b[11;3HIf your host doesn't have a registered DNS name, enter its IP address here.\u001b[13;2HServerName www.example.com:80\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[15;2H\u001b[69X\u001b[16;3HDeny access to the entirety of your server's filesystem. You must\u001b[5X\u001b[17;3Hexplicitly permit access to web content directories in other \u001b[9X\u001b[18;3H<Directory> blocks below.\u001b[50X\u001b[19;2H\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Directory\u001b[m\u000f /\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\r\n\u001b[m\u000f    \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f none\r\n    \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all denied\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</Directory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[35X\r\n \n\u001b[67X\u001b[26;3HNote that from this point forward you must specifically allow\u001b[9X\u001b[27;3Hparticular features to be enabled - so if something's not working as\u001b[6X\u001b[28;3Hyou might expect, make sure that you have specifically enabled it\u001b[5X\u001b[29;3Hbelow.\u001b[8X\r\n\n\u001b[23X\n#\n \u001b[30m\u001b[103mDoc\u001b[m\u000fumentRoot: The directory out of which you will serve your\u001b[34;3Hdocuments. By default, all requests are taken from this directory, but\u001b[35;3Hsymbolic links and aliases may be used to point to other locations.\r\n\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mDoc\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mumentRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/srv/http\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[54X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Directory\u001b[m\u000f \"/srv/http\"\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[53X\r\n    #\u001b[10X\r\n    # Possible values for the Options directive are \"None\", \"All\",\r\n    # or any combination of:\r\n    #   Indexes Includes FollowSymLinks SymLinksifOwnerMatch ExecCGI MultiViews\r\n    #\r\n    # Note that \"MultiViews\" must be named *explicitly* --- \"Options All\"\r\n    # doesn't give it to you.\u001b[30X\r\n    #\u001b[7X\r\n    # The Options directive is both complicated and important.  Please see\r\n    # http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/core.html#options\u001b[7X\r\n    # for more information.\u001b[32X\r\n    #\r\n    \u001b[96mOptions\u001b[m\u000f Indexes FollowSymLinks\r\n\u001b[9X\n    #\r\n    # AllowOverride controls what directives may be placed in .htaccess files.\r\n    # It can be \"All\", \"None\", or any combination of the keywords:\r\n    #   AllowOverride FileInfo AuthConfig Limit\r\n    #\u001b[73X\r\n    \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f None\u001b[50X\r\n\u001b[75X\n    #\u001b[65X\r\n    # Controls who can get stuff from this server.\r\n    #\r\n    \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all granted\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</Directory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30X\r\n \u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f251,3          45%\u001b[67;5H\u001b[?25h"]
