[2122.672519, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[65A\u001b[74X\u001b[3;2H\u001b[64X\u001b[4;3HDocumentRoot: The directory out of which you will serve your\u001b[9X\u001b[5;3Hdocuments. By default, all requests are taken from this directory, but\u001b[6;3Hsymbolic links and aliases may be used to point to other locations.\u001b[7;2H\u001b[50X\r\n\u001b[96mDocumentRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/srv/http/arteri\"\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Directory\u001b[m\u000f \"/srv/http/arteri\"\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[37X\r\n        \u001b[96mOptions\u001b[m\u000f FollowSymLinks\u001b[46X\r\n        \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f All\u001b[25X\r\n        \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all granted\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</Directory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[60X\r\n    #\u001b[71X\r\n    # Possible values for the Options directive are \"None\", \"All\",    \r\n    # or any combination of:\u001b[44X\r\n    #   Indexes Includes FollowSymLinks SymLinksifOwnerMatch ExecCGI MultiViews\r\n    #\u001b[72X\r\n    # Note that \"MultiViews\" must be named *explicitly* --- \"Options All\"\r\n    # doesn't give it to you.\r\n    #\r\n    # The Options directive is both complicated and important.  Please see\r\n    # http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/core.html#options\r\n    # for more information.\r\n    #\u001b[63X\r\n    \u001b[96mOptions\u001b[m\u000f Indexes FollowSymLinks\u001b[38X\r\n\u001b[76X\n    #\u001b[67X\r\n    # AllowOverride controls what directives may be placed in .htaccess files.\r\n    # It can be \"All\", \"None\", or any combination of the keywords:\r\n    #   AllowOverride FileInfo AuthConfig Limit\r\n    #\r\n    \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f None\r\n\u001b[71X\n    #\u001b[50X\r\n    # Controls who can get stuff from this server.\r\n    #\u001b[73X\r\n    \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all granted\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[41;3HDirectoryIndex: sets the file that Apache will serve if a directory\r\n# is requested.\r\n\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<IfModule\u001b[m\u000f dir_module\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[46X\r\n    \u001b[96mDirectoryIndex\u001b[m\u000f index.html\u001b[30X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</IfModule>\u001b[m\u000f \r\n \n\u001b[66X\u001b[49;3HThe following lines prevent .htaccess and .htpasswd files from being \u001b[50;2H viewed by Web clients. \u001b[51;2H\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Files\u001b[m\u000f \".ht*\"\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[53;5H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all denied\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</Files>\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[57;3HErrorLog: The location of the error log file.\u001b[31X\u001b[58;3HIf you do not specify an ErrorLog directive within a <VirtualHost>    \u001b[59;3Hcontainer, error messages relating to that virtual host will be\u001b[10X\u001b[60;3Hlogged here.  If you *do* define an error logfile for a <VirtualHost>\u001b[61;3Hcontainer, that host's errors will be logged there and not here.\r\n\n\u001b[96mErrorLog\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/var/log/httpd/error_log\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[42X\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f280,1          51%\u001b[?112c\u001b[?1002h\u001b[?1006h\r\u001b[33A\u001b[?25h"]
