[2527.700519, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000fi"]
[2527.70724, "o", "\u001b[H \u001b[2;3H'Main' server configuration\u001b[45X\u001b[3;2H\u001b[64X\u001b[4;3HThe directives in this section set up the values used by the 'main'  \u001b[5;3Hserver, which responds to any requests that aren't handled by a\u001b[6;4HVirtualHost> definition.  These values also provide defaults for\u001b[7;3Hany <VirtualHost> containers you may define later in the file.\u001b[9;3HAll of these directives may appear inside <VirtualHost> containers,\u001b[10;3Hin which case these default settings will be overridden for the\u001b[11X\u001b[11;3Hvirtual host being defined.\u001b[21X\r\n\n\u001b[72X\u001b[14;2H\u001b[75X\u001b[15;3HServerAdmin: Your address, where problems with the server should be \u001b[16;3He-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such  \u001b[17;3Has error documents.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\u001b[23X\u001b[18;2H\u001b[76X\r\n\u001b[96mServerAdmin\u001b[m\u000f you@\u001b[96mexample\u001b[m\u000f.com\u001b[17X\u001b[22;9HName gives the name and port that the server uses to identify itself.\u001b[23;3HThis can often be determined automatically, but we recommend you specify\u001b[24;2H it explicitly to prevent problems during startup.\u001b[25;2H\u001b[67X\u001b[26;3HIf your host doesn't have a registered DNS name, enter its IP address here.\u001b[27;2H\u001b[75X\nServerName www.example.com:80\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[16X\n\n# Deny access to the entirety of your server's filesystem. You must\r\n# explicitly permit access to web content directories in other \u001b[33;2H <\u001b[30m\u001b[103mDi\u001b[m\u000frectory> blocks below.\u001b[34;2H\u001b[70X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mDi\u001b[0;10;1m\u000frectory\u001b[m\u000f /\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[42X\r\n    \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f none\r\n    \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all denied\u001b[56X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mDi\u001b[0;10;1m\u000frectory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[64X\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[41;3HNote that from this point forward you must specifically allow\r\n# particular features to be enabled - so if something's not working as\u001b[43;2H you might expect, make sure that you have specifically enabled it\u001b[44;3Hbelow.\u001b[59X\u001b[45;2H\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[12X\u001b[48;3HDocumentRoot: The directory out of which you will serve your\u001b[5X\u001b[49;3Hdocuments. By default, all requests are taken from this directory, but\u001b[50;2H symbolic links and aliases may be used to point to other locations.\u001b[51;2H\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[96mDocumentRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/srv/http/arteri\"\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mDi\u001b[0;10;1m\u000frectory\u001b[m\u000f \"/srv/http/arteri\"\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\r\n\u001b[m\u000f        \u001b[96mOptions\u001b[m\u000f FollowSymLinks\r\n        \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f All\u001b[12X\r\n        \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all granted\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mDi\u001b[0;10;1m\u000frectory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[66X\r\n    #\u001b[67X\r\n    # Possible values for the Options directive are \"None\", \"All\",\u001b[9X\r\n    # or any combination of:\u001b[42X\r\n    #   Indexes Includes FollowSymLinks SymLinksifOwnerMatch ExecCGI MultiViews\r\n    #\r\n    # Note that \"MultiViews\" must be named *explicitly* --- \"Options All\"\r\n    # doesn't give it to you.\u001b[13X\r\n    #\u001b[66;224H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f36,4          42%\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
