[2923.801593, "o", "\u001b[?25lD"]
[2923.808204, "o", "\u001b[1;2H It is usually good practice to create a dedicated user and group for\u001b[2;3Hrunning httpd, as with most system services.\u001b[25X\u001b[3;2H\u001b[54X\r\n\u001b[96mUser\u001b[m\u000f http\r\n\u001b[96mGroup\u001b[m\u000f http\u001b[68X\r\n\u001b[76X\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</IfModule>\u001b[m\u000f    \r\n \u001b[9;3H'Main' server configuration\r\n#\n The directives in this section set up the values used by the 'main'\u001b[12;3Hserver, which responds to any requests that aren't handled by a  \u001b[13;3H<VirtualHost> definition.  These values also provide defaults for\u001b[14;3Hany <VirtualHost> containers you may define later in the file.\u001b[16;3HAll of these directives may appear inside <VirtualHost> containers,\u001b[17;3Hin which case these default settings will be overridden for the\u001b[18;2H virtual host being defined.\u001b[19;2H\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[9X\n#\n ServerAdmin: Your address, where problems with the server should be\u001b[23;3He-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such\u001b[24;2H as error documents.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\u001b[25;2H\u001b[77X\r\n\u001b[96mServerAdmin\u001b[m\u000f you@\u001b[96mexample\u001b[m\u000f.com\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[28;2H\u001b[69X\u001b[29;3HServerName gives the name and port that the server uses to identify itself.\u001b[30;2H This can often be determined automatically, but we recommend you specify\u001b[31;3Hit explicitly to prevent problems during startup.\u001b[32;2H\u001b[41X\n If your host doesn't have a registered \u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[m\u000fNS name, enter its IP address here.\r\n#\u001b[51X\nServerName www.example.com:80\u001b[27X\r\n\u001b[55X\n#\u001b[53X\n \u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[m\u000feny access to the entirety of your server's filesystem. You must\u001b[39;2H explicitly permit access to web content directories in other \u001b[40;2H <\u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[m\u000firectory> blocks below.\u001b[26X\u001b[41;2H\u001b[60X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[0;10;1m\u000firectory\u001b[m\u000f /\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[41X\r\n    \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f none\u001b[32X\r\n    \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all denied\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[0;10;1m\u000firectory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[53X\u001b[47;2H\u001b[56X\n Note that from this point forward you must specifically allow\r\n# particular features to be enabled - so if something's not working as\u001b[50;2H you might expect, make sure that you have specifically enabled it\u001b[51;2H below.\u001b[49X\r\n#\u001b[59X\r\n\u001b[54X\u001b[54;2H\u001b[52X\n \u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[m\u000focumentRoot: The directory out of which you will serve your\u001b[56;2H documents. By default, all requests are taken from this directory, but\u001b[57;2H symbolic links and aliases may be used to point to other locations.\u001b[58;2H\u001b[44X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mocumentRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/srv/http/arteri\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[24X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[0;10;1m\u000firectory\u001b[m\u000f \"/srv/http/arteri\"\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[31X\r\n        \u001b[96mOptions\u001b[m\u000f Indexes FollowSymLinks\u001b[23X\r\n        \u001b[96mAllowOverride\u001b[m\u000f All\u001b[32X\r\n        \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all granted\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mD\u001b[0;10;1m\u000firectory>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[49X\r\n    #\u001b[46X\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f229,42         40\u001b[67;3H\u001b[?25h"]
[2924.284836, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000fu"]
[2924.291685, "o", "\u001b[1;2H\u001b[69X\u001b[2;3HMutex: Allows you to set the mutex mechanism and mutex file directory\u001b[3;2H for individual mutexes, or change the global defaults\r\n#\u001b[8X\r\n# Uncomment and change the directory if mutexes are file-based and the default\r\n# mutex file directory is not on a local disk or is not appropriate for some\r\n# other reason.\r\n#\u001b[9;3HMutex default:/run/httpd   \r\n \n\u001b[68X\u001b[12;3HListen: Allows you to bind Apache to specific IP addresses and/or\u001b[13;3Hports, instead of the default. See also the <VirtualHost>\u001b[8X\u001b[14;3Hdirective.\u001b[52X\u001b[16;3HChange this to Listen on specific IP addresses as shown below to   \u001b[17;3Hprevent Apache from glomming onto all bound IP addresses.\u001b[6X\u001b[18;2H\u001b[28X\nListen 12.34.56.78:80\r\n\u001b[96mListen\u001b[m\u000f 80\r\n \n\u001b[68X\u001b[23;3HDynamic Shared Object (DSO) Support\u001b[33X\u001b[24;2H\u001b[48X\n To be able to use the functionality of a module which was built as a DSO you\r\n# have to place corresponding `LoadModule' lines at this location so the\r\n# directives contained in it are actually available _before_ they are used.\u001b[28;2H Statically compiled modules (those listed by `httpd -l') do not need\u001b[29;3Hto be loaded here.\u001b[57X\u001b[30;2H\u001b[73X\u001b[31;3HExample:\u001b[41X\u001b[32;2H LoadModule foo_module modules/mod_foo.so\u001b[33;2H\u001b[76X\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f mpm_event_module modules/mod_mpm_event.so\u001b[35;2HLoadModule mpm_prefork_module modules/mod_mpm_prefork.so\r\n#LoadModule mpm_worker_module modules/mod_mpm_worker.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f authn_file_module modules/mod_authn_file.so\u001b[38;2HLoadModule authn_dbm_module modules/mod_authn_dbm.so\u001b[14X\u001b[39;2HLoadModule authn_anon_module modules/mod_authn_anon.so\u001b[8X\u001b[40;2HLoadModule authn_dbd_module modules/mod_authn_dbd.so\u001b[41;2HLoadModule authn_socache_module modules/mod_authn_socache.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f authn_core_module modules/mod_authn_core.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f authz_host_module modules/mod_authz_host.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f authz_groupfile_module modules/mod_authz_groupfile.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f authz_user_module modules/mod_authz_user.so\r\n#LoadModule authz_dbm_module modules/mod_authz_dbm.so\u001b[47;2HLoadModule authz_owner_module modules/mod_authz_owner.so\u001b[48;2HLoadModule authz_dbd_module modules/mod_authz_dbd.so\u001b[10X\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f authz_core_module modules/mod_authz_core.so\u001b[16X\u001b[50;2HLoadModule authnz_ldap_module modules/mod_authnz_ldap.so\u001b[10X\u001b[51;2HLoadModule authnz_fcgi_module modules/mod_authnz_fcgi.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f access_compat_module modules/mod_access_compat.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f auth_basic_module modules/mod_auth_basic.so\u001b[54;2HLoadModule auth_form_module modules/mod_auth_form.so\u001b[55;2HLoadModule auth_digest_module modules/mod_auth_digest.so\u001b[5X\u001b[56;2HLoadModule allowmethods_module modules/mod_allowmethods.so\u001b[13X\u001b[57;2HLoadModule file_cache_module modules/mod_file_cache.so\u001b[14X\u001b[58;2HLoadModule cache_module modules/mod_cache.so\r\n#LoadModule cache_disk_module modules/mod_cache_disk.so\r\n#LoadModule cache_socache_module modules/mod_cache_socache.so\r\n#LoadModule socache_shmcb_module modules/mod_socache_shmcb.so\r\n#LoadModule socache_dbm_module modules/mod_socache_dbm.so\r\n#LoadModule socache_memcache_module modules/mod_socache_memcache.so\r\n#LoadModule socache_redis_module modules/mod_socache_redis.so\r\n#LoadModule watchdog_module modules/mod_watchdog.so\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f97,1            6\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
